			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Mortar is a workable paste that hardens to bind building blocks such as stones, bricks, and concrete masonry units. It has different types and uses in ancient and modern construction, such as lime, gypsum, and Portland cement. Mortar can be a noun or a verb, and it can refer to a sturdy vessel, a muzzle-loading weapon, or a plastic building material. It is a material you can use in construction to hold or stick pieces of masonry together to form a structure.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">砂浆是一种可加工的糊状物，硬化后可粘结石块、砖块和混凝土砌体等建筑材料。它在古代和现代建筑中有不同的类型和用途，如石灰、石膏和波特兰水泥。灰泥既可以是名词，也可以是动词，可以指坚固的容器、枪口射击的武器，也可以指塑料建材。它是一种建筑材料，可以用来将砖石固定或粘在一起形成结构。</common:generalComment>
